records.addlTxt:
Defendant Travous D Kelly in court with attorney Darryl E. Smith.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  PSI reviewed and corrections made.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

The Court sentenced the defendant to serve  9 MONTHS at the House of Corrections straight time with 2 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence.
Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 2 YEARS probation.

  Conditions of Probation:
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department.
- Absolute/maintain sobriety, no alcohol, no drugs.
- No possession/consumption/selling/distribution of illegal drugs/alcohol.
- Random urine screens.
- No violations of the law rising to the level of probable cause
- Obtain/maintain fulltime employment
- No contact with:  Tereasa S or Jorga M
- Provide a DNA sample.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.
- perform 30 hours of community service
- no contact with weapons
- write letters of apology within 30 days
- cognitive therapy and any other recommended treatments

Court suspends defendant right to vote until they are restored.
Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Restitution in the amount of $1392.19 to Tereasa S and $909.00 to Jorga M; 
All court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA) and all applicable fees of supervision are waived.  Court finds payment of restitution is paramount and does not assess any other costs.
-  No Cash Bail Posted in this matter 

Filed:  
Victim Impact Statements

Court finds the defendant was under the age of 25 at the time of the offense, the charge is a Class H/I felony, society would not be harmed and the defendant would benefit by expungement.  Court grants expungement upon successful completion of the sentence.

Defendant Travous D Kelly in court with attorney Darryl E. Smith.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared on behalf of DeAnn L. Heard for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  State cannot proceed to sentencing on today's date as victim notification was not done; requested another date.

Request for Substitution of Judge received and filed.  Court consented to substitution against Judge Rothtstein.  Parties are advised the Clerk of Circuit Court reassigned case pursuant to current court rules to Judge Dennis Cimpl, Br. 19, in Room 313 of the Safety Building.     Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 19 and ordered all terms and conditions of bail to continue.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 12, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
